desc: Drop-in at the Downtown Community Centre for pick-up Badminton and Pickleball games. This is a safe space to try out both racket sports for all skills levels. This is a free program for youth ages 12-17 with no registration required. Youth are invited to bring their own rackets or borrow equipment on site!
age_description: Age at least 12 yrs but less than 18 yrs,
name: Youth Drop-in Badminton and Pickleball

desc:
This is a non-competitive recreational, all level play of pickleball where sixes style is played, 3 on 3 with two players at the back and one player at the kitchen line. When the numbers warrant, sixes will be played across all three courts. If participant numbers are low, doubles may be played. Pickleball at CHCC is a recreation program offered by CHRA and we value good sportsmanship. This style of play promotes teamwork in a fun and friendly atmosphere.
Registration not required. Drop-in program and pay as you play. First come, first serve. Waiver to be signed at front desk. Cap of 24.
age_description: Age at least 18 yrs but less than 99 yrs,
name: All Level Pickleball Drop-In

desc:
Learn how to play pickleball! Program will involve skill practice, learning of the game, and a chance to play in doubles against others! You can bring your own paddle if you would like but this is not necessary. This is a low participant program focused on skill development and learning of the game.

Programs in gym 2 and 3 at the community centre do not have viewing access.

Only registered participants are allowed in the program

Please note after March 4, the program will only be in Gym 2
name: Adult Intro to Pickleball

desc: All levels of pickleball are welcome. Paddles are available for use. $2.00/visit.

desc: All levels of pickleball are welcome. Paddles are available for use. $2.00/visit.
name: Pickleball Drop In

desc:
This is a more competitive recreational level of play. Requires higher skill level and experience. No beginners. This session consists of sixes play, 3 on 3 during the first hour and doubles play for the second hour. This promotes a more inclusive and community feel with intermediate pickleball skills as well as providing a fast-paced competitive doubles play during the second hour. While the skill level is high, this is a recreation program where good sportsmanship must be maintained at all times.
Registration not required. Drop-in program and pay as you play. First come, first serve. Waiver to be signed at front desk. Cap of 20.
age_description: Age at least 18 yrs but less than 99 yrs,
name: Pickleball Drop-In - Intermediate

desc: All levels of pickleball are welcome. Paddles are available for use. $2.00/visit.
name: Pickleball Drop In

desc: This program is designed for new players. You will receive instruction, learn new skills, and play one of the fastest growing sports in the country. Paddles are available for use. Drop in is available if program is not at the maximum registered players.
name: Pickleball-Intro for Beginners

desc: This program is designed for new players. You will receive instruction, learn new skills, and play one of the fastest growing sports in the country. Paddles are available for use. Drop in is available if program is not at the maximum registered players.
name: Pickleball-Intro for Beginners

desc: This course covers the most important parts of the game. Serve, serve receive, third shot drop, drop shot, the volley, positioning, tactics, and responsibilities.
name: Pickleball for New Players to Beginners

desc: This course takes the player past the basics of the game. Review of court responsibilities, positioning and team tactics. Improvement of technique, drop shot, block volley, resets, smash, lob and lob retrieval.
name: Pickleball for Beginner Plus to Intermediate

desc: This is a supportive and inclusive pickleball program for persons living with dementia or experiencing memory loss. Players will have the opportunity to develop skills, participate in related activities, and play non-competitive games of simplified pickleball. This program will also provide good exercise, great fun and social connections. Players can be supported by trained staff/volunteers or caregivers are welcome to join in on the fun. Additional participant information is required prior to program starting.
name: Simplified Pickleball

desc: This course covers the most important parts of the game. Serve, serve receive, third shot drop, drop shot, the volley, positioning, tactics, and responsibilities.
name: Pickleball for New Players to Beginners

desc: This course takes the player past the basics of the game. Review of court responsibilities, positioning and team tactics. Improvement of technique, drop shot, block volley, resets, smash, lob and lob retrieval.
name: Pickleball for Beginner Plus to Intermediate

desc:
Pickleball is a mix of badminton, ping pong and tennis played on an indoor court. It is designed to be easy to learn and play whatever age and ability you are. There is some availability for paddles. Balls are not provided.

Withdrawals from single-visit programs must be done by 11:59pm the day before the program to qualify for a refund, transfer or account credit.
name: Pickleball

desc: For players who are interested in developing some new skills and team tactics.  Emphasis on third shot drop, short shot, reset short, punch/block volley, responsibilities, positioning and questions dealing with rules and strategy.
name: Pickleball Clinic for Beginner Plus

desc: This clinic is for players who have been playing for awhile and understand the basics of the game. Proper footwork will be introduced to create a more consistent game. Focus will be on consistent deep serves, return of serves and third shot drops. Time will be spent on developing a consistent forehand and backhand while playing the net game. Position on the court and placement over power will be emphasized.
name: Pickleball Clinic for Intermediate Players

desc:
This program is suited for the newer player with some basic understanding of the game. There is no instruction during this time, but it will allow you to play the game with other beginner level participants. There is some availability for paddles and balls.

desc:

desc:
Intermediate Plus: This program is played with 4 people per court, rotation between courts is permitted. Registrants receive 1 hour 20 minutes of play. Intermediate Plus players position themselves well on the court, move to the net quickly, make shots that are usually concise and hit with power. They understand a hard and soft game, hit third shot drops regularly and work with their partner to win a point. If required, paddles and balls are available.

Advanced: This program is played with 4 people per court, rotation between courts is permitted. Registrants receive 1 hour 20 minutes of play. Advanced players apply strategies well, can expect opponents’ shots and hit shots with varying speed and control. They usually play at the volley net, can sustain 20-30 hits without difficulty and can selectively place shots. They are patient, move as a team with their partner, and can cover most of the court. If required, paddles and balls are available.

An adult must accompany children under 14 years of age.
name: Pickleball - Intermediate Plus/Advanced - RIM Park

This program is played with 4 people per court, rotation between courts is permitted. Registrants receive 1 hour 20 minutes of play; all skill levels are welcome. If needed, paddles and balls are available. It is helpful to understand the rules, and the basics of how to play.

An adult must accompany children under 14 years of age.
name: Pickleball - Open - RIM Park

desc: New to the sport of pickleball? Learn to play clinics introduce users to the game of pickleball, one of the fastest growing and popular sports. Participants leave the clinic with an understanding of basic rules, fundamental skills, game etiquette and how to keep score.
age_description: Age at least 18 yrs but less than 99 yrs,

desc:
Played 2 vs 2; open play. Check out one of the fastest growing sports; don’t have a partner? Sign up as an individual, weekly commitment is required to participate. The league consists of 12 weeks of play, multiple matches per night, game times are: 6:00 p.m., 7:00 p.m., 8:00 p.m., and 9:00 p.m. 8 teams per time slot. All teams will be required to play at all timeslots as they will rotate on a weekly basis; this league is self-officiated.

Location: Activity Court, WMRC

Skill level descriptions:
Recreational – newer to the sport and love it
Novice – some experience playing
Intermediate – Have played it for a bit and am learning the rules and tricks of the sport
Advanced – Lots of experience and some tournament play
name: Pickleball League - Mondays - Free Agent - Spring 2025

desc:
